#   cryo is the **operator-friendly bulk-extraction tool for
#   Ethereum-compatible chains** — pulls every typed `eth_*` +
#   `trace_*` + `debug_*` JSON-RPC datatype into typed
#   columnar files for typed downstream typed data-warehouse
#   ingest.  Use cases:
#
#     • **Chain-wide indexer feed** to a typed data warehouse
#       (typed BigQuery / typed Snowflake / typed ClickHouse /
#       typed Redshift / typed DuckDB / typed Spark / typed
#       Trino / typed Presto / typed Dremio) — typed cryo
#       output is typed directly typed Parquet-loadable
#     • **Per-protocol forensic extraction** — typed `cryo
#       logs --contract 0x... --topic0 0x...` typed pulls all
#       typed Transfer / Approval / Sync / Swap / Mint / Burn
#       events for a typed specific contract + topic
#     • **Custom protocol research** — typed `cryo
#       eth_calls --function totalSupply()` typed pulls
#       typed periodic typed contract-state snapshots
#     • **Historical reconstruction** — typed `cryo state_reads`
#       typed pulls typed full typed pre-state + typed post-
#       state for every typed transaction (the typed
#       `eth_call`-replay approach)
#     • **MEV research** — typed `cryo blocks --include-columns
#         all` pulls typed full typed block data including
#       typed mev-boost typed builder + typed proposer typed
#       fee distribution
#     • **Re-org-aware indexing** — typed `--reorg-buffer`
#       typed waits N blocks before typed committing typed
#       chunks to typed disk (typed safe against typed Ethereum
#       1-block typed reorgs that would otherwise typed
#       corrupt typed downstream indexes)
